04/05/2004
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- Croatia wants to develop economic co-operation with Kosovo, Croatian Chamber of Economy head Adan Vidosevic said Monday (3 May).
In meetings with Kosovo Parliament Speaker Nexhat Daci and Prime Minister Bajram Rexhepi, Vidosevic said Croatian busineses look forward to the renewal of the privatisation process in Kosovo and are interested in investing in the province.
In other news, Swedish Brigadier General Anders Braennstroem is cautioning against troop reductions in Kosovo.
In an interview Monday, he said a strong foreign military presence would be needed for years to eliminate the danger of ethnic cleansing.
Braennstroem led the Swedish forces in Kosovo until last month.
(HINA, FoNet, AFP - 03/05/04)
